    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fabric surfaces with a soft, napped quality, similar to the skin of a peach, created by brushing the face of a dense twill or satin weave. This surface may be found on fabrics in silk, cotton, or other artificial fibers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
